<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><refentry version="5.0-subset Scilab" xml:id="imlaplacian" xml:lang="en" xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><refnamediv><refname>imlaplacian</refname><refpurpose>Compute a Laplacian image response.</refpurpose></refnamediv><refsynopsisdiv><title>Syntax</title><synopsis>out = imlaplacian(image); out = imlaplacian(image, alpha)</synopsis></refsynopsisdiv><refsection><title>Parameters</title><variablelist><varlistentry><term>image</term><listitem><para>Input image converted to a numeric filtering plane.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term>alpha</term><listitem><para>Laplacian kernel parameter from 0 to 1. Default is 0.2.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term>out</term><listitem><para>Numeric Laplacian response.</para></listitem></varlistentry></variablelist></refsection><refsection><title>Description</title><para><function>imlaplacian</function> applies the IPCV <function>fspecial</function> Laplacian kernel with <function>imfilter</function>.</para></refsection><refsection><title>Examples</title><programlisting><![CDATA[image = imread(fullpath(getIPCVpath() + "/images/coins_gray.jpg")); response = imlaplacian(image); imshow(mat2gray(response));]]></programlisting></refsection><refsection role="see also"><title>See also</title><simplelist type="inline"><member><link linkend="fspecial">fspecial</link></member><member><link linkend="imfilter">imfilter</link></member></simplelist></refsection><refsection><title>Authors</title><simplelist type="vert"><member>Tan Chin Luh</member></simplelist></refsection><refsection><title>History</title><informaltable border="1"><tr><td>Version</td><td>Description</td></tr><tr><td>5.0.0</td><td>Function introduced in development Step 3.</td></tr></informaltable></refsection></refentry>
